rrator|Disfruté cada sorbo de mi café mientras observaba la gente pasar.\",\n  \"n|narrator|El ambiente tranquilo del café era perfecto para relajarme.\",\n  \"n|narrator|Después de disfrutar mi café y pastel, pagué y me despedí con gratitud.\",\n]"}], "prompt": "\nSTORY: Create a(an) story in Latin American Spanish where I am sitting outdoors in a Colombian cafe ordering coffee and a pastry. This story involves myself and the waiter. The story should be appropriate for beginning-level language instruction. \n  \nThe story must contain between 8 to 12 lines, reflecting a natural flow for a story. The story should contain no fewer than 8 lines. The story should follow a simple narrative arc in the past tense, using first- or third-person narration. The story should describe a brief experience or encounter and be grounded in everyday vocabulary.\n\nSTORY RESPONSE: Your story response should be an array of strings that takes the form,\n\n  [\n  \"n|narrator|Line from the story\",\n  \"n|narrator|Another line from the story\",\n  \"n|narrator|Yet another line from the story\"\n]\n\nwhere each line uses three fields separated by ''|'':\n\n- Gender (\"n\"), which is neutral and fixed for the narrator,\n- Role of narrator, which is fixed for non-dialog lesson prompt styles,\n- The line of story content.\n  \nFormatting rules:\n\n  - output must be well-formed JSON,\n  - no trailing commas,\n  - no single quotes,\n  - use double quotes only,\n  - no Markdown wrappers,\n  - no comments,\n  - no introductions,\n  - no wrapping phrases,\n  - no partial JSON blocks,\n  - no explanatory text or prose, and\n  - no headings, titles, or labels.\n\nImportant: Do not include a comma after the last item in the JSON array. Trailing commas will cause the response to be rejected.\n\nYour story response must be a single valid JSON array that starts with a left bracket \"[\" and ends with a right bracket \"]\". Do not prepend phrases like “Here is your JSON:”. Assume the consumer is a machine expecting strict JSON compliance.\n\nA complete example of a story response follows:\n\n[\n  \"Juan llegó a París por primera vez y se sentó en un café.\",\n  \"Vio a un camarero pasar y decidió pedir un café.\",\n  \"Mientras esperaba, observaba la vida parisina pasar.\",\n  \"El café llegó humeante y perfecto para el momento.\"\n]\n\n\n", "status": "warning", "success": true, "sentinel": "", "moduleProse": "n|narrator|Estaba sentado en un café al aire libre en Colombia. n|narrator|Decidí pedir un café y un pastel al camarero. n|narrator|El camarero amablemente tomó mi pedido y regresó con una sonrisa. n|narrator|Me entregó el café humeante y el delicioso pastel. n|narrator|Disfruté cada sorbo de mi café mientras observaba la gente pasar. n|narrator|El ambiente tranquilo del café era perfecto para relajarme. n|narrator|Después de disfrutar mi café y pastel, pagué y me despedí con gratitud.", "moduleDurationMs": 1685.647291958332}', '2025-07-03 00:11:57.009048+00', '2025-07-03 00:11:57.009048+00');
